<task id="WKSP-052" project="spaarke-workspace-user-configuration-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Implement workspace loading states and error handling</title>
    <phase>6</phase>
    <tags>frontend, fluent-ui</tags>
    <estimated-effort>5h</estimated-effort>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <dependencies>032, 051</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>E</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    <role>Senior developer implementing workspace personalization</role>
    <goal>Implement three distinct loading states for the workspace: first visit (no saved layouts), returning user (fetching layout), and fetch failure (graceful degradation).</goal>
    <context>
      The workspace needs polished loading behavior for three scenarios:

      1. First visit (no saved layouts): The user has never personalized their workspace. Render the
         system default layout immediately (no loading state needed) and show a subtle
         "Personalize your workspace" banner with a link to open the Layout Wizard.

      2. Returning user: The user has saved layouts. Show a Fluent skeleton/shimmer effect in the
         workspace grid area while the layout data is being fetched from the API or sessionStorage.

      3. Fetch failure: The API call fails. Fall back to the cached layout (if available from
         sessionStorage) or the system default layout. Show an inline Fluent Toast notification
         informing the user that their custom layout couldn't be loaded.

      These states ensure the workspace never shows a blank screen or an unhandled error.
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - First visit MUST render system default immediately + "Personalize your workspace" banner
      - Banner MUST link to Layout Wizard (open via Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo)
      - Returning user MUST show Fluent SkeletonItem/Shimmer in workspace grid during fetch
      - Skeleton layout MUST approximate the grid structure (not a single full-page shimmer)
      - Fetch failure MUST fall back to cached layout or system default (never blank screen)
      - Fetch failure MUST show an inline Toast notification (Fluent useToastController)
      - MUST use Fluent UI v9 components (SkeletonItem, MessageBar, Toast) per ADR-021
      - All states MUST render correctly in both light and dark themes
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <relevant-files>
    <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/LegalWorkspaceApp.tsx</file>
    <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/</file>
  </relevant-files>
  <steps>
    <step id="1">Create a WorkspaceSkeleton component that renders Fluent SkeletonItem elements in a grid layout approximating the workspace structure (header skeleton + grid cell skeletons).</step>
    <step id="2">Create a PersonalizeBanner component: subtle MessageBar with "Personalize your workspace" text and an action link that opens the Layout Wizard via Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo.</step>
    <step id="3">Update the useWorkspaceLayouts hook to expose a status field: "loading" | "loaded" | "error" | "first-visit" based on fetch state and whether any user layouts exist.</step>
    <step id="4">Update LegalWorkspaceApp to render based on status: "first-visit" shows system default + PersonalizeBanner, "loading" shows WorkspaceSkeleton, "loaded" shows WorkspaceShell, "error" triggers fallback + toast.</step>
    <step id="5">Implement the error fallback: try sessionStorage cache first, then SYSTEM_DEFAULT_LAYOUT. Dispatch a Fluent Toast notification ("Couldn't load your workspace layout. Showing default.") using useToastController.</step>
    <step id="6">Ensure all three states render correctly in both light and dark themes. Verify skeleton colors use Fluent design tokens.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>First visit renders system default immediately with "Personalize your workspace" banner</criterion>
    <criterion>Returning user sees skeleton/shimmer grid while layout fetches</criterion>
    <criterion>Fetch failure falls back to cached layout or system default without blank screen</criterion>
    <criterion>Fetch failure shows an inline toast notification about the fallback</criterion>
    <criterion>All loading states render correctly in both light and dark Fluent themes</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
